---
title: Payment Received Flow
config:
  layout: elk
  look: handDrawn
  theme: dark
---

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as 👤 User
    participant UI as 🖥️ AddPaymentReceivedModal
    participant View as 📊 outstanding_invoice_view
    participant Hook as 🎣 useAuth/usePerms
    participant Supabase as 📡 Supabase
    participant DB as 💾 PostgreSQL
    participant Audit as 📋 Auditlog
    
    User->>UI: 1. Click "Payment Received"
    
    Hook->>Supabase: 2. Fetch outstanding invoices
    Supabase->>View: 3. Query outstanding_invoice_view
    Note over View: Calculates:<br/>outstanding = invoice_value - paid_amount
    
    View->>DB: 4. LEFT JOIN invoices & payments
    DB-->>View: 5. Return with calculations
    View-->>Supabase: 6. Return unpaid invoices
    Supabase-->>Hook: 7. Filter invoices > 0
    Hook-->>UI: 8. Return outstanding invoices
    
    UI-->>User: 9. Show outstanding invoices list
    User->>UI: 10. Select invoice
    UI-->>User: 11. Show invoice details + outstanding amount
    
    User->>UI: 12. Enter payment amount
    User->>UI: 13. Enter payment date & method
    User->>UI: 14. Click "Save Payment"
    
    UI->>UI: 15. Validate payment
    Note over UI: • Amount <= outstanding<br/>• Valid date<br/>• Payment method selected
    
    alt Validation Failed
        UI-->>User: 16. Show error (over-payment not allowed)
    else Validation Passed
        UI->>Supabase: 17. INSERT into payments_received
        
        Supabase->>DB: 18. INSERT payment record
        Note over DB: invoice_id, payment_amount,<br/>payment_date, payment_method,<br/>reference_number
        
        DB-->>Supabase: 19. Return success
        Supabase-->>UI: 20. Payment recorded
        
        UI->>Audit: 21. logExport(category=PAYMENT)
        Audit->>Supabase: 22. INSERT into audit_logs
        Supabase->>DB: 23. INSERT audit record
        DB-->>Supabase: 24. Confirmed
        
        Note over DB: === AUTO-CALCULATION ===
        
        DB->>View: 25. View recalculates outstanding
        Note over View: NEW outstanding =<br/>invoice_value - (paid + new_payment)
        
        View-->>DB: 26. Updated view state
        
        Note over DB: === REAL-TIME BROADCAST ===
        
        DB->>DB: 27. Broadcast INSERT event
        Supabase->>Supabase: 28. Listen to postgres_changes
        Supabase-->>UI: 29. Emit real-time update
        UI->>UI: 30. Update Dashboard state
        
        UI->>UI: 31. Close modal
        UI-->>User: 32. Show success notification
        User->>User: 33. View updated Dashboard
        Note over User: Outstanding amount<br/>decreased by payment
    end
    
    Note over DB: === MULTI-PAYMENT SCENARIO ===
    
    rect rgba(100, 149, 237, 0.2)
    Note over DB: Same invoice can receive<br/>multiple payments over time
    Note over DB: Each INSERT updates view<br/>outstanding total is recalculated
    end
    
    style User fill:#1e40af,stroke:#3b82f6,color:#fff
    style UI fill:#059669,stroke:#10b981,color:#fff
    style View fill:#7c3aed,stroke:#a78bfa,color:#fff
    style Hook fill:#dc2626,stroke:#f87171,color:#fff
    style Supabase fill:#ea580c,stroke:#fb923c,color:#fff
    style DB fill:#d97706,stroke:#fbbf24,color:#fff
    style Audit fill:#b91c1c,stroke:#fca5a5,color:#fff
